    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to special ornate capital letters in illuminated manuscripts marking the beginning of a section of text such as a verse or paragraph. In modern calligraphy the term is applied to capitals built up by inking between pen strokes and having serifs in the form of long, thin, straight lines.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
